gomodel:SYNGO_5110  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4a-d: SNX26 (ARHGAP33) and PSD95 (DLG4) interact through SNX26-PX and -RhoGAP domains.\n\nFigure g,h: overexpressed SNX26 (ARHGAP33) co-localized with PSD95 (DLG4) at dendritic spines in cultured hippocampal neurons. Endogenous SNX26 targeted with an antibody showed (reduced) co-localization with PSD95.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Immunoprecipitation assays with brain lysates showed that SNX26 bound to PSD-95 in rat brains (Fig. 4F)\"\n\nantibody:\nSNX26 (Abcam). Anti-SNX26 mouse antibody was provided by Dr. Tadashi Yamamoto (University of Tokyo)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5110" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

